benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: Valid Request coverage: multiple scenarios cover successful resume with required headers and optional parameters (TC01-TC04, TC18, TC24, TC26).
Non-Existing Resource coverage: 404 when no bundle exists (empty database) (TC05).

Input Validation coverage: tests for invalid bundleId format (TC06), missing required header (TC07), extra/unexpected parameters (TC11), invalid pluginProperty format (TC19), and past date handling (TC20).
State Validation coverage: tests preventing resume from active (TC08) or cancelled (TC09) bundles.
Authorization coverage: tests for missing/invalid authentication (TC07, TC10).
Concurrency coverage: test for concurrent PUT requests (TC21).
Server/Dependency error coverage: 500 when dependencies fail (TC14) and 504 when plugin service degraded (TC25).
Large payload/limits coverage: maximum header length (TC12) and large pluginProperty values (TC13).
Security coverage: SQL injection (TC16) and XSS in X-Killbill-Comment header (TC17).
Partial input coverage: resume with only required fields (TC18).
Date handling coverage: future date scheduling (TC02) and past date rejection (TC20).
Performance coverage: test under load/response time (TC22).
Regression/Backward compatibility coverage: legacy headers (TC24) and previously fixed edge cases (TC23).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling tests are not covered.
Caching headers for PUT (ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested.
Invalid date format tests are missing (beyond past/future checks).
BundleId length boundary tests are not present.
Duplicate submissions/idempotency edge cases beyond current tests are not covered.
Deeper audit-log verification beyond reason (e.g., exact entries) is not covered.
More extensive concurrent load scenarios beyond two simultaneous requests are not covered.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to ensure proper throttling and error handling for bursts.
Include caching behavior checks for PUT, such as validating ETag/Cache-Control headers if applicable.
Add tests for invalid date formats and bundleId length boundary scenarios.
Expand concurrency tests with more clients and varied timing to simulate real-world load, including random ordering.
Enhance audit-log verification to confirm exact entries for reason, comment, and creator voter roles.
Add tests for duplicate submissions/idempotency to ensure consistent outcomes on retries.
